Returns a new Mesh that is watertight and 3D printable. As a result of making a Mesh watertight, self-intersections, overlaps, and non-manifold geometry is removed from the mesh. The method computes a thin-band distance field and generates a new Mesh using marching cubes but doesn't project back onto the original Mesh. Basically the Mesh is filled with a bunch of tiny boxes, and a new mesh is created around this.

Annotations.Title: Views from Points on the building
Annotations.DescriptionText: The view from a point on a window is computed.

Annotations.Title: Visible Target Voxels
Annotations.DescriptionText: The visible part of the skydome is approximated by intersecting the voxels visible from a point with all voxels that are part of the skydome.

Annotations.Title: Percent of target that is visible
Annotations.DescriptionText: The Vertical Sky Component metric is approximated by dividing the number of visible skydome voxels by the total number of skydome voxels.

Annotations.Title: Voxel Model Axes
Annotations.DescriptionText: A set of axes is to created for all voxel models.

Annotations.Title: Analysis Extents
Annotations.DescriptionText: A set of extents large enough to contain the skydome plus padding is created to ensure the visibility computation has sufficient range.

Annotations.Title: Voxels for Visibility
Annotations.DescriptionText: The voxel model representing the building and context is resized to contain the entire skydome.

Annotations.Title: Target Voxels
Annotations.DescriptionText: The skydome voxels are identifed by voxelizing the spheres and filling the region between them.
